      <p permid="ees">
        Hint: there are two base cases <m>P(0)</m> and <m>P(1)</m>.
        Then, for the inductive case,
        assume <m>P(k)</m> is true for all <m>k \lt n</m>.
        This allows you to assume <m>a_{n-1} = 1</m> and <m>a_{n-2} = 1</m>.
